faculty /ˈfækəltɪ/

(faculties) 

1. N-COUNT Your faculties are your physical and mental abilities. 机能 

例： He was drunk and not in control of his faculties. 他喝醉了，控制不了他的各项机能。 

2. N-VAR A faculty is all the teaching staff of a university or college, or of one department. 全体教员 [美国英语] 

例： The faculty agreed on a change in the requirements. 全体教员同意改变要求。 

例： How can faculty improve their teaching so as to encourage creativity? 全体教员怎样才能改进教学以便激发创造力？

